  "title": "QUANTITY SURVEYOR",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview</strong></p><p>Fast Flow is a highly specialised group of companies providing solutions for rainwater management in building projects across Asia Pacific. Fast Flow designs siphonic and hybrid drainage systems that seamlessly integrate into a host building, optimizing material use and achieving both architectural and engineering expectations. We have a team of highly skilled engineers and designers who are committed to create drainage solutions that add value to our clients’ building projects. Exceeding all drainage requirements while providing a host of benefits to even the most complex of buildings – this is …the art of drainage</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>The Quantity Surveyor supports post-contract administration by managing quantity surveying tasks, sub-contracting processes, payment claims, certifications, and reporting to ensure project budget and cost control align with Company Guidelines and SOP.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Analyze project drawings to perform accurate material take-offs to support cost estimation and procurement</li><li>Manage sub-contractor and vendor processes including issuing RFQs, evaluating tenders, preparing work orders, and certifying claims to ensure timely and compliant contract execution</li><li>Administer contract variations, retentions, and final accounts to maintain financial control and contractual compliance</li><li>Coordinate client-related contract matters including performance bonds, warranties, material breakdowns/SOR, payment claims, certifications, and variations to uphold client satisfaction and contractual obligations</li><li>Support project budget monitoring and cost control by tracking expenditures and identifying variances for corrective action</li><li>Prepare detailed internal reports to communicate project financial status and support decision-making</li><li>Execute ad hoc tasks as assigned to contribute to project and company objectives</li></ul>",
